data.chText: 真实
data.enText: connected with real things

data.chText: 实际的；真实的；客观存在的
data.enText: connected with real situations rather than with ideas or theories

data.chText: 获得实际工作经验
data.enText: to have gained practical experience of the work

data.chText: 切实的忠告 / 帮助 / 支持
data.enText: practical advice/help/support

data.chText: 实际问题
data.enText: practical problems

data.chText: 这项研究有一些明显的实际用途。
data.enText: There are some obvious practical applications of the research.

data.chText: 具体点说，那意味着少花些钱。
data.enText: In practical terms , it means spending less.

data.chText: 实际一点看，这里不是理想的住处。
data.enText: From a practical point of view, it isn't a good place to live.

data.chText: 可行
data.enText: likely to work

data.chText: 切实可行的

before.enText: of an idea, a method or a course of action

data.enText: right or sensible; likely to be successful

data.chText: 我们跑那么远只为了去度个周末实在很不切实际。
data.enText: It wouldn't be practical for us to go all that way just for the weekend.

data.chText: 有用
data.enText: useful

data.chText: 有用的；适用的
data.enText: useful or suitable

data.chText: 理想的城市实用小汽车
data.enText: a practical little car, ideal for the city

data.chText: 理智
data.enText: sensible

data.chText: 明智的；实事求是的
data.enText: sensible and realistic

data.chText: 咱们实际一点儿，先计算一下成本费用。
data.enText: Let's be practical and work out the cost first.

data.chText: 长于制作
data.enText: good at making things

data.chText: 心灵手巧的；善于制作（或修补）的
data.enText: good at making or repairing things

data.chText: 鲍勃心灵手巧，家里的零活他都包了。
data.enText: Bob's very practical. He does all the odd jobs around the house.

data.chText: 几乎全部
data.enText: almost total

data.chText: 几乎完全的；实际上的
data.enText: almost complete or total

data.chText: 她等于是嫁了个陌生人。
data.enText: She married a practical stranger.
for (all) practical purposes

data.chText: 事实上；其实
data.enText: used when you are stating what the reality of a situation is

data.chText: 比赛虽然还有十分钟，但实际上等于已经结束了。
data.enText: There's still another ten minutes of the game to go, but for practical purposes it's already over.

data.chText: 实习课；实践课；实验考核
data.enText: a lesson or an exam in science or technology in which students have to do or make things, not just read or write about them

ex.chText: 唯一可行的做法是把会议推迟。
ex.enText: The only practicable course of action is to delay the meeting.

ex.chText: 精确复制也不一定总是行得通。
ex.enText: It may not always be practicable to copy exactly.

synonyms.bx: 指在某一情况下行得通的。

ex.chText: 政府需要一个可行的解决方法。
ex.enText: The government needs a practical solution.

ex.chText: 全神贯注是达到更高效率的切实有效的方法。
ex.enText: Concentration is a practical way of achieving greater efficiency.

synonyms.bx: 指计划、方法等因正确合理而极有可能取得成功或发挥作用的。

data.enText: for (all) practical purposes

data.chText: 事实上；其实
data.enText: used when you are stating what the reality of a situation is

data.chText: 比赛虽然还有十分钟，但实际上等于已经结束了。
data.enText: There's still another ten minutes of the game to go, but for practical purposes it's already over.

tr: having or put to a practical purpose or use
concerned with actual use or practice
example: he is a very practical person
the idea had no practical application

tr: guided by practical experience and observation rather than theory
example: a hardheaded appraisal of our position
completely practical in his approach to business

value.def: The practical aspects of something involve real situations and events, rather than just ideas and theories.

example.ex: We can offer you practical suggestions on how to increase the fibre in your daily diet...
example.tran: 我们能就如何增加你日常饮食中的纤维素量提供实际的建议。

example.ex: This practical guidebook teaches you about relaxation, coping skills, and time management.
example.tran: 这本实用的旅行指南教给你放松的方法、处理问题的技巧以及如何安排时间。

value.def: You describe people as practical when they make sensible decisions and deal effectively with problems.

example.ex: You were always so practical, Maria...
example.tran: 玛丽亚，你以前一向很注重实效。

example.ex: How could she be so practical when he'd just told her something so shattering?...
example.tran: 他刚把这么令人震惊的事情告诉她，她怎么会如此理智呢？

example.ex: He lacked any of the practical common sense essential  in management.
example.tran: 管理方面基本的实用常识他一点也不懂。

value.tran: （人）明智的，注重实效的，务实的

value.def: Practical ideas and methods are likely to be effective or successful in a real situation.

example.ex: Although the causes of cancer are being uncovered, we do not yet have any practical way to prevent it...
example.tran: 虽然癌症的病因正被逐步揭开，但我们尚未有任何切实可行的办法来预防它。

example.ex: It is not easy to make practical suggestions for helping her.
example.tran: 要提出切实可行的建议帮助她并不容易。

value.tran: （意见和方法）切实有效的，可行的

value.def: You can describe clothes and things in your house as practical when they are suitable for a particular purpose rather than just being fashionable or attractive.

example.ex: Our clothes are lightweight, fashionable, practical for holidays.
example.tran: 我们的服装轻便、时尚，并且很适合度假时穿。

value.tran: （衣物等）实用的，适合特定用途的

value.def: A practical is an examination or a lesson in which you make things or do experiments rather than simply writing answers to questions.
value.tran: 实验课；实践课；实验考核
